Yes, by failing to enforce its own policies and resolutions, the UN is in danger of becoming a non-entity in the parts of the world that need its guidance most. Similarly, how many slaves did the signing of the emancipation proclamation free?  Zero.  Not a single slave was set free by Pres. Lincoln's signing, because all the slaves were in territories not controlled by the Union. War was fought to enforce that policy.<br>
